I pretended I was just working from home while a worker fixed the kitchen floor, actually editing *Hooked*.
If only this damn file could open. (OneDrive is really fucking useless.)
*The hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the sound was super loud. Fantastic.
I turned the air purifier to max, which felt a bit overbearing, but I did smell sawdust, so it wasn't entirely unreasonable to do so, especially since he refused to wear a mask. Plus, I really do need to protect myself, don't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can only sleep after he leaves.
The good news is, Chapter 4 is finally edited!
Chapter 5 is quite long and super anxiety-inducing. Yay! It's so thrilling.
Searching and replacing…➡️ellipsis, there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But I still need to stick to this. Most natural languages are disjointed, especially when people are emotionally charged.
There's a floor repairman using a vacuum cleaner, hoping it means he's about to finish.
He went out (it sounded like he was cutting something). I peeked at the progress. There's still a lot to do :(
Chapter five has seven pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the draft is in good shape, mainly just some adjustments in layout, as well as minor modifications to active voice and conciseness. But I really need a break, a cup of tea, and that guy is still busy in my kitchen.
He started using the vacuum cleaner again. I hope that's a good sign.
The worker who was fixing the kitchen floor has gone!
He told me that he quoted the price for repairing the entire floor, but the landlord is too penny-pinching and only agrees to pay for the repair of the part by the door that was already rotten. It feels much better.
I was drinking tea in the garden while the air purifier in the kitchen worked hard to clean the air in the room!
